cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper focuses on procedurally generating interactive fiction worlds using natural language, which involves tasks related to natural language processing, artificial intelligence, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural language generation models, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves human participant-based evaluations, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves knowledge graph completion, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves generating coherent and interesting narratives, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
